      "id": 1,
      "text": "St. Augustine South sits within the Jacksonville Metropolitan Statistical Area, linking it to one of Florida’s largest urban regions.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        26
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._Augustine_South%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The city was founded in September 1565 by Spanish explorer Pedro Menéndez de Avilés, making it one of the earliest European settlements in the Americas.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6,
        9
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.visitflorida.com/places-to-go/northeast/st-augustine/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "St. Augustine South is part of the oldest continuously inhabited European‑established settlement in the continental United States.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        20
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.visitflorida.com/places-to-go/northeast/st-augustine/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The magnificent Castillo de San Marcos, a 17th‑century fort, remains a key landmark that showcases the city’s colonial military history.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://dos.fl.gov/historical/explore/el-camino-real/places-to-go/st-augustine/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Visitors can explore the Fountain of Youth Archaeological Park, where early Spanish explorers are believed to have sought legendary rejuvenation.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        19
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.visitflorida.com/places-to-go/northeast/st-augustine/"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "The Augustine Lighthouse & Maritime Museum offers panoramic views of the Atlantic and tells the story of the region’s maritime heritage.",
